PART D — CLARIFICATIONS

Q: I am a PhD student at a university. Do I need a commercial license?
A: No. Academic research is Non-Commercial Use.

Q: I work at a national observatory. We use COMETH to process public
   telescope data for published research. Do I need a commercial license?
A: No, if the research is publicly funded and results are published.
   Yes, if you use it to provide paid data-processing services to third
   parties.

Q: I want to include COMETH in my company's satellite image analysis
   pipeline. Do I need a commercial license?
A: Yes. Internal operational use by a for-profit entity requires a
   commercial license.

Q: Can I try COMETH before buying a commercial license?
A: Yes. The demo notebook and open-source code are fully functional for
   evaluation. Contact us for a 30-day commercial evaluation license.

Q: I'm not sure if my use case is commercial or non-commercial.
A: Email cometh@proton.me with a brief description. We'll clarify
   within 2 business days.
